1) Springfield XDS case

3) Extra backstrap

8) Versacarry IWB holster

They don't make them like this anymore !

I think this rifle was made in the early 80's, but not positive. It has been in the box, in my safe for more years than I can remember and only taken out of box occasionally to oil. This gun is NEW, with factory trigger tag attached.

This rifle has one of the prettiest stocks you will see, with beautiful checkering and rosewood forend cap. * I have some beautiful pictures of this rifle, but my main computer is down, so I don't have access to them. I'll post some from my phone, but they won't do it justice.
NO TRADES - $750.00 cash - Thanks for looking and Merry Christmas !"

**Hi Point lifetime warranty**

This firearm has never been sent in for repair but I have a 9mm hi point that I got at a gun show that was beat to crap (I think it was kept in a tool box or something) but still functioned without a problem.

I sent it the manufacturer to be ""checked for problems that might have escaped my attention"" -- I would have been fine if they determined nothing was broken and sent it back as is but they completely refurbished it!

It came back with new grips, slide, sites and compensator and I suspect they replaced some internal parts such as the pin, springs, etc. They also sent me a box, gun-lock and owners manual. (that I didn't have with it).
I can't remember how long it took ... maybe three weeks? They're much faster than Taurus is with their warranty and easier to work with as well.
Ever since that experience I've felt really good about having hi points.
Sure I prefer my more pricey guns but I think most of the hate towards this brand is mostly snobbery.
If anyone has a problem with them the factory will fix it."
